  <section>
    <h2>Path A MVP: End-to-end SCE RSS bridge</h2>
    <p>We’re building a distributed, offline-first knowledge commons that federates advocacy and education across peer-to-peer networks using Conflict-free Replicated Data Types (CRDTs).</p>
  </section>
  <section>
    <h3>Download Bridge Artifacts</h3>
    <p>Qwn’s upcoming GitHub repository contains the foundational GO-KC bridge implementations. Use the link below to access the repository once it’s released.</p>
    <p><a href="https://github.com/Qwn/GO-KC" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Download Qwn's GO-KC Repository (Upcoming)</a></p>
  </section>
  <section>
    <h3>Local Sovereignty (PGLite Sovereignty)</h3>
    <p>GO-KC upholds a local-first sovereignty model grounded in PGLite, enabling operators to retain cognitive control, privacy, and data integrity even in disrupted environments. This is achieved by embedding a CRDT-based Living Web Document, ensuring peer-to-peer synchronization without central points of failure.</p>
  </section>
  <section>
    <h3>What’s Next</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Publish durable artifacts to Zenodo via the Defender Publication Hook (Defensive Publication).</li>
      <li>Coordinate with communities to scale the mesh while preserving autonomy.</li>
    </ul>
